      <bioghist id="aspace_4c584284ebf1d41e93c0b33ad654166e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Communications Committee of the Yale University Library was formed in 2003 by the Library Management Council and the Microcosm Group. Its charge and mission is to support and promote an environment of two way communication by recommending, advising on and facilitating the exchange of ideas, the availability of information, and the use of good communication methods and skills.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5bf38a4911b7d5aa7653a261f8bbc138">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes, correspondence, reports, and bulletins documenting the mission and activities of the Yale University Library Communications Committee.</p>
      </scopecontent>
